+# Live In-Play CTMC Trading Stack
+
+Institutional architecture for live football probability extraction, risk, and execution.
+
+## Architecture
+
+```
+[ LIVE DATA FEEDS ] → [ JSON PARSER ] → [ EVENT STACK (Redis / memory) ]
+                                              │
+              ┌───────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┐
+              ▼                               ▼                               ▼
+   [ QUANT ENGINE: 15s CTMC tick ]   [ SENTIMENT — future ]        [ EXCHANGE MARKS ]
+              │                               │                               │
+              └───────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────┘
+                                              ▼
+                               [ EXECUTION ENGINE (Kelly gate) ]
+                                              ▼
+                               [ SMART ORDER ROUTER (paper / live stub) ]
+```
+
+## Math (v1)
+
+State vector \(X(t) = (G_H, G_A, P, R_H, R_A)\) at minute \(t\).
+
+Hazard rates:
+
+\[
+\lambda_H(t) = \alpha_H \cdot \gamma_{\text{home}} \cdot \delta(t) \cdot \exp\left(\sum_i w_i f_i(t)\right)
+\]
+
+Terminal 1X2 via truncated-score CTMC + matrix exponentiation (`inplay/ctmc.py`) or Monte Carlo (`inplay/monte_carlo.py`).
+
+Execution uses quarter-Kelly with VAR/penalty suspension gates (`inplay/risk.py`).
+
+## Module map
+
+| Module | Role |
+|--------|------|
+| `inplay/state.py` | Match state vector + fixture parsing |
+| `inplay/features.py` | Rolling xG momentum, possession tilt, corners |
+| `inplay/intensity.py` | \(\lambda_H, \lambda_A\) with time-decay spikes at 44′ / 89′ |
+| `inplay/ctmc.py` | Generator \(Q(t)\), forward Kolmogorov solver |
+| `inplay/monte_carlo.py` | 10k–100k Poisson path simulation |
+| `inplay/event_stack.py` | Redis tick ring (in-memory fallback) |
+| `inplay/engine.py` | 15s quant tick orchestrator |
+| `inplay/risk.py` | Fractional Kelly + suspension rules |
+| `inplay/execution.py` | Paper/live execution + JSONL audit |
+| `inplay/router.py` | Multi-venue order splitter (FIX adapters plug-in) |
+| `inplay/integration.py` | Dashboard + API wiring |
+
+## Enable
+
+```bash
+# .env
+HIBS_INPLAY_ENABLED=1
+HIBS_INPLAY_TICK_SEC=15
+HIBS_INPLAY_SOLVER=ctmc          # or mc
+HIBS_INPLAY_MC_PATHS=10000
+HIBS_INPLAY_KELLY_FRACTION=0.25
+HIBS_INPLAY_MIN_EDGE=0.025
+# Optional Redis event stack
+# HIBS_INPLAY_REDIS_URL=redis://127.0.0.1:6379/0
+```
+
+## API
+
+`GET /api/inplay/probabilities` — live CTMC 1X2 + Kelly signals for in-play fixtures.
+
+Optional `?ids=123,456` filter.
+
+## Worker
+
+```bash
+bash scripts/run_inplay_quant_worker.sh
+```
+
+Paper execution audit: `logs/inplay_execution.jsonl` when `HIBS_INPLAY_WORKER_EXECUTE=1`.
+
+Live routing requires `HIBS_INPLAY_EXECUTE=live` and `HIBS_INPLAY_CONFIRM_LIVE=YES` (venue adapters are stubs until wired).
+
+## Roadmap (not in v1)
+
+- Opta / Sportradar binary feed handlers (sub-ms parse)
+- Sentiment scraper lane (injury / red-card social reaction)
+- Rust/C++ intensity kernel for &lt;50ms tick latency
+- Pinnacle / Betfair FIX adapters in `router.py`
+- GPU batch MC (100k paths / 15s)
+- Trained \(w_i\) from rolling Poisson regression on tick archive
